crops.description: Received in the importation of 1897 (8 packages). Large, roundish fruits; yellow with some green splashes and faint, sparse netting; flesh white; not ripe when obtained.

Received in the importation of 1897 (68 packages). Large, oval fruits with smooth skin; white with a few short green splashes; the largest noted at 29} by 21} inches in circumference; flesh white. A winter keeper, fit for preserving; not ripe when obtained. Reported as brought from Charchan (No. 1), near Batoum.
Received in the importation of 1897 (4 packages). Winter melon; round; yellow marbled with green. Noted as originally from Crimea.
Received in the importation of 1897 (11 packages). Oval fruits, green and yellow marbled, smooth, and very good; identified as Persian.
Received in the importation of 1897 (8 packages). Winter melon; center solid; flesh white (good); described as small, black, green-wrinkled; Crimean.

Received in the importation of 1897 (14 packages). Tiflis–Erivan, No. 2. Oval, smooth, yellow fruits, somewhat mottled with small dark-green spots; flesh white; very large at 30 by 23 inches in circumference. Not quite ripe when obtained, but sweet. Described as a 'Doutjma' melon (see No. 739).
Received in the importation of 1897 (18 packages). Local name: Eichen (oak). Large, roundish fruits; dark green, marbled with faint yellowish; flesh white. Green when obtained; a late keeper.
Received in the importation of 1897 (7 packages). Local name: Crimean pineapple. Oval; yellow with some green; marbly; white-fleshed; very good.
Received in the importation of 1897 (15 packages). Winter type; small; white; skin wrinkled; flesh white; center solid; very good; noted as Crimean (?).
Received in the importation of 1897 (6 packages). Tiflis, No. 4. Oval fruits, 28} by 20 inches in circumference; bright yellow and smooth.

Received in the importation of 1897 (33 packages). Tiflis, No. 1. Oval fruits, 20} by 27 inches in circumference; skin longitudinally furrowed; white, covered with short green splashes and spots; white-fleshed; not ripe when obtained; long-keeping.
